ProtoDefines:
. "A sequence $\{s_n\}$ converges to a limit $s$ if for every 
   $\epsilon>0$ there is an integer $N$ such that $ 
   |s_n-s|<\epsilon n\ge N. $ In this case we say that 
   $\{s_n\}$ is convergent and write $$ \lim_{n\to\infty}s_n=s.
   $$ A sequence that does not converge diverges, or is 
   divergent"
